  <HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef ParentName="HumanResources.UpdateFeatureBase">
    <defName>HumanResources_1_0</defName>
    <assemblyVersion>1.0</assemblyVersion>
    <targetAudience>NewPlayers</targetAudience>
    <content>
      |&lt;b&gt;WELCOME TO HUMAN RESOURCES!&lt;/b&gt;
      |People now only know what they have learned! Here's a quick guide to get you started:
      |
      |img:TechButton
      |Check out the new tab for your colonists. It displays the sum of their knowledge, and that represents the limit of what they are able to build, repair, craft, grow and also the weapons they are able to equip. A starting knowledge set is generated for every pawn based on background, age and faction. From there, its your task to educate them!
      |
      |img:Study+Shelf
      |Build a &lt;i&gt;study desk&lt;/i&gt; and a &lt;i&gt;bookshelf&lt;/i&gt; as soon as you can. This allows your colonists to &lt;i&gt;document&lt;/i&gt; their knowledge into books and then &lt;i&gt;study&lt;/i&gt; books to acquire new knowledge (when assigned to the &lt;i&gt;study&lt;/i&gt; work type).
      |
      |img:HomeworkIndicator,HomeworkOnTree
      |You must assign them study and document tasks individually. You can do that by clicking directly on the desired technologies on their Tech tabs or on the main Research screen, where you can also assign &lt;i&gt;research&lt;/i&gt; tasks.
      |
      |img:ResearchBenches
      |For research, you'll still need research benches, but they have been slimmed down to better fit alongside your library. Keep in mind what your researchers learn remain only in their heads until they can write a book on their discoveries. Only when that book is archived on a bookshelf you will really have unlocked that technology.
      |
      |img:NetworkServer,NetworkTerminal
      |Physical books will only get you so far. To deal with space-age knowledge, you'll need information-age infrastructure. On the late game, get ready to build your very own &lt;i&gt;network server&lt;/i&gt; to host your library and the accompanying &lt;i&gt;network terminal&lt;/i&gt; for uploading and downloading digital knowledge!
      |
      |img:Target+Dummy
      |When you discover new weapons, your colonists will need to train at these facilities in order to learn how to use them (for that, they must also be assigned to &lt;i&gt;study&lt;/i&gt;). The &lt;i&gt;training dummy&lt;/i&gt; is for meleee weapons and the &lt;i&gt;target stand&lt;/i&gt; is for ranged ones.
      |You can also task them with &lt;i&gt;practicing&lt;/i&gt; a weapon - which will allow them to sharpen their melee or shooting skills - or &lt;i&gt;experimenting with an unknown weapon&lt;/i&gt; - which is &lt;b&gt;a very risky business!&lt;/b&gt; If sucessful, this will allow your colonists to equip a weapon that's more advanced than the current colony knowledge, but at a high risk of damaging the weapon in the process... or getting hurt themselves!
      |
      |For more details on how to play with this mod and how it works, check out the wiki on our GitHub page. The link is in the description.
      |
      |Enjoy!
      |
      |img:Passion|caption:&lt;b&gt;Please, consider supporting the making of this mod!&lt;/b&gt;
      |If you are able to contribute, you can buy me a coffee on &lt;i&gt;https://ko-fi.com/jptrrs&lt;/i&gt;, or follow the link above for our Patreon page, where you can also find &lt;b&gt;more mods&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;add-ons&lt;/b&gt; that aren't on Steam!
      |Many, many thanks!
    </content>
  </HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef>

  <HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef ParentName="HumanResources.UpdateFeatureBase">
    <defName>HumanResources_1_1</defName>
    <assemblyVersion>1.1</assemblyVersion>
    <content>
      |&lt;b&gt;Weapons proficiency revision!&lt;/b&gt;
      |- &lt;i&gt;Clutter cleared.&lt;/i&gt;   I've changed the rules for displaying weapons on the proficiency list at the Tech tab. Artillery and common weapons (such as bottles) will now only show up when filtered for. Turret guns were excluded, since they can't really be equipped.
      |- &lt;i&gt;No more free bows and arrows.&lt;/i&gt;  Colonists no longer start knowing how to wield simple weapons that didn't require training from inferior tech levels. Instead...
      |- &lt;i&gt;Tech-enabled common weapons.&lt;/i&gt;  Now there is a middle-ground between training-required weapons and those simply known by anyone. These "easy" weapons will become available to your colonists as soon as their corresponding technology is added to your library, no training required. &lt;i&gt;All Artillery and mounted weapons&lt;/i&gt; will now follow that logic. If you know any modded weapons that also fit that bill, let me know and I might include them.
      |There were other unrelated bugfixes and improvements. Check the change notes on our Steam page for a complete list.
      |
      |img:Passion|caption:&lt;b&gt;Please, consider supporting the making of this mod!&lt;/b&gt;
      |If you are able to contribute, you can buy me a coffee on &lt;i&gt;https://ko-fi.com/jptrrs&lt;/i&gt;, or follow the link above for our Patreon page, where you can also find &lt;b&gt;more mods&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;add-ons&lt;/b&gt; that aren't on Steam!
      |Many, many thanks!
    </content>
  </HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef>

  <HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef ParentName="HumanResources.UpdateFeatureBase">
    <defName>HumanResources_1_2</defName>
    <assemblyVersion>1.2</assemblyVersion>
    <content>
      |&lt;b&gt;Bridging the Gap revision!&lt;/b&gt;
      |- &lt;i&gt;Slaves tightened up.&lt;/i&gt;   The same knowledge restrictions that apply to your regular colonists will now also affect your slaves. They had too much of a slack!
      |- &lt;i&gt;Better feedback on Tech Levels and research costs.&lt;/i&gt;  Unlike vanilla, with &lt;i&gt;HR&lt;/i&gt; your faction's starting tech level doesn't affect your research costs. But the the Research Tree UI didn't get the memo. We've fixed this, so the techs' cost and tooltips are now accurate.
      |img:TLindicator
      |What &lt;b&gt;does&lt;/b&gt; affect your research is your researcher's personal tech level. To make that clearer, we've put this indicator on their &lt;i&gt;Tech&lt;/i&gt; tab to show where their expertise stands. Also, the cost for the individual techs displayed there will now be dynamically calculated, varying from pawn to pawn and according to the work they put in. Hover your mouse over that number to see a breakdown of those calculations.
      |On top of that, we've added and improved compatibility to a couple of mods. Check the change notes on our Steam page for a complete breakdown.
      |
      |img:Passion|caption:&lt;b&gt;Please, consider supporting the making of this mod!&lt;/b&gt;
      |If you are able to contribute, you can buy me a coffee on &lt;i&gt;https://ko-fi.com/jptrrs&lt;/i&gt;, or follow the link above for our Patreon page, where you can also find &lt;b&gt;more mods&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;add-ons&lt;/b&gt; that aren't on Steam!
      |Many, many thanks!
    </content>
  </HugsLib.UpdateFeatureDef>

